00:09:34.730 --> 00:09:37.120
&gt;&gt; Christina Bashford: The song
we just heard echoes another

00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:39.980
recruitment song about
loyalty to King and Country

00:09:39.980 --> 00:09:42.650
by British composer Paul Reubens.

00:09:42.650 --> 00:09:46.780
It was published in London
by Chappell Co in late 1914.

00:09:46.780 --> 00:09:49.580
Just weeks after the British
Government had declared war

00:09:49.580 --> 00:09:53.710
on Germany and had kicked off
a major recruitment campaign

00:09:53.710 --> 00:09:58.610
which Reuben's song refers
to and subtly manipulates.

00:09:58.610 --> 00:10:02.800
It was immensely popular and surely
helped establish a role for women

00:10:02.800 --> 00:10:04.920
in the bid to enlist young men.

00:10:04.920 --> 00:10:08.850
A role that would become highly
visible in Britain within months.

00:10:08.850 --> 00:10:10.150
And also in Canada.

00:10:19.490 --> 00:10:23.090 position:56%
In entering the war, Britain was
not only aligning itself with France

00:10:23.090 --> 00:10:26.770
and Russia against German and
Austria-Hungarian aggression,

00:10:26.770 --> 00:10:28.440
it was also creating the crux

00:10:28.440 --> 00:10:30.830
of what became known
as the Allied Forces.

00:10:30.830 --> 00:10:32.730
And defending its position

00:10:32.730 --> 00:10:36.790
as the world's pre-eminent
imperialist power.

00:10:36.790 --> 00:10:41.190
Over the course of the war,
a staggering 2.7 million men

00:10:41.190 --> 00:10:44.440
from the British colonies
would serve the British army.

00:10:44.440 --> 00:10:49.300
Fighting for a tiny island
thousands of miles away.

00:10:49.300 --> 00:10:52.440
Now one of the signal features
of the so-called great war,

00:10:52.440 --> 00:10:55.470
is that it was not one
conflict, but many fought

00:10:55.470 --> 00:10:57.920
in several parts of the world.

00:10:57.920 --> 00:11:01.750
Thus, Japan soon entered on the
side of the alliance pushing back

00:11:01.750 --> 00:11:06.320
against German naval ships in
the Pacific and Indian Oceans.

00:11:06.320 --> 00:11:12.240
However, in August 1914, with the
British military under resourced,

00:11:12.240 --> 00:11:14.730
the Colonial armies were
all that Britain could count

00:11:14.730 --> 00:11:18.730
on to defend its territorial
interests.

00:11:18.730 --> 00:11:20.330
&gt;&gt; Gayle Sherwood Magee: When
Britain declared war on August 4,

00:11:20.330 --> 00:11:26.250 position:56%
2914, Canada had an
insubstantial army of 3000 soldiers.

00:11:26.250 --> 00:11:29.880
Through the late summer and
fall of 1914 men from most parts

00:11:29.880 --> 00:11:31.960
of the country rushed to enlist.

00:11:31.960 --> 00:11:36.140
Within one year 35,000 troops
were fighting in Europe.

00:11:36.140 --> 00:11:40.800
Music, often British, resolutely
fed the recruitment drive.

00:11:40.800 --> 00:11:44.970
For King and Country was issues
in a Colonial edition in Toronto.

00:11:44.970 --> 00:11:46.280
Together with a piano version

00:11:46.280 --> 00:11:49.700
with an all-purpose red,
white, and blue cover.

00:11:49.700 --> 00:11:53.020
Despite an official show of unity
and allegiance to Great Britain,

00:11:53.020 --> 00:11:56.240
however, the first World War
would deeply divide Canada along

00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:59.180
linguistic, political,
and religious fault lines.

00:11:59.180 --> 00:12:02.100
Particularly between the
anglophone half of the country

00:12:02.100 --> 00:12:03.780
and the roughly quarter
of the nation

00:12:03.780 --> 00:12:07.430
that claimed French
as it's main language.

00:12:07.430 --> 00:12:09.000
&gt;&gt; Christina Bashford:
By April 1915,

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:12.760 position:56%
it was clear that the war had
become to become that expected to be

00:12:12.760 --> 00:12:16.490
over by Christmas was looking
like a much longer term haul.

00:12:16.490 --> 00:12:20.360
A significant development
came in May when Italy,

00:12:20.360 --> 00:12:23.910
which had initially been poised
to support the Central Powers,

00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:28.130
switched allegiance and entered
the war on the other side.

00:12:28.130 --> 00:12:34.270
This moment was crystalized in
music by one Francesco Paolo Tosti.

00:12:34.270 --> 00:12:38.770
Tosti was an Italian born singer
and prolific song composer

00:12:38.770 --> 00:12:42.540
who had settled in London
and become a British citizen.

00:12:42.540 --> 00:12:45.230
He'd had a successful career
and had even been knighted.

00:12:45.230 --> 00:12:49.990
He was living in retirement in
Italy when Britain declared war.

00:12:49.990 --> 00:12:53.360
And shortly after Italy
entered he wrote his one

00:12:53.360 --> 00:12:57.860
and only political song,
The Allies March to Freedom.

00:12:57.860 --> 00:13:00.460
Which we'll hear in a moment.

00:13:00.460 --> 00:13:05.700
Chappell published it with Italy
and English text and a lavish cover

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:09.410
that depicted the flags of the
major allies, Britain, France,

00:13:09.410 --> 00:13:11.890
Belgium, Russia, and Japan.

00:13:11.890 --> 00:13:13.380
We see it here.

00:13:13.380 --> 00:13:17.750
The Italian flag at it's center,
snuggled close to the Union Jack

00:13:17.750 --> 00:13:22.300
with gleaming finials that seemed
to be standing next to bayonets,

00:13:22.300 --> 00:13:26.390 position:56%
which for now at least were still
the soldiers' quintessential weapons

00:13:26.390 --> 00:13:28.220
of war.

00:13:28.220 --> 00:13:30.790
Chappell who'd already
published many

00:13:30.790 --> 00:13:34.600
of Tosti's songs could
expect to trade on his name.

00:13:34.600 --> 00:13:36.440
But the firm might also have hoped

00:13:36.440 --> 00:13:39.000
to market the work to
Italian immigrants.

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:44.740
There were nearly 20,000
Italians living in London in 1915.

00:13:44.740 --> 00:13:48.380
We should note, too, the
American import stamp.

00:13:48.380 --> 00:13:51.120
And that the song was
sold in the U.S.

00:13:51.120 --> 00:13:54.450
where Italian immigrants
were much more numerous.

00:13:54.450 --> 00:13:57.700
And where that population
might also have been willing

00:13:57.700 --> 00:14:00.000
in spirit to join the march.

